node.text: We closed on our new house today! 🎉I can’t believe it! What a whirlwind the last two months have been! I wanted to give you a full home tour of the empty house before we move in this weekend Stay tuned until the very end...that’s when I share the big project we have planned for the house and one of the main reasons why we decided to move! We can’t wait to move in, get settled, and begin sharing this new adventure with all of you! ❤️🏡

node.text:
Today I’m sharing a walk through of my entire house (every single room!), which I’ve actually never done before on my page! I’m sharing rooms I’ve never shown before including my laundry room and mud room! 

If you missed it, we are selling our house! Get all the info on our move on my website, Mytexashouse.com. All sources are linked on the LIKEtoKNOW.it app or by clicking the link in my IG bio!

*update: House sold. We moved! 

#hometour #realestate #houseforsale #mytexashouse #texashomes #texasrealestate #falldecor #homedecor

node.title: We’re Selling Our House!: A Complete Home Tour of “Mytexashouse”!

node.text: Here’s my super easy way to put on a duvet cover! No more actually climbing inside of the duvet to install it! 🙈😂 The first step, which isn’t shown, is to turn the duvet cover INSIDE OUT! Then lay the duvet insert over the cover and tie all four sides of the duvet to the insert! Roll them like a burrito. Turn back out the ends like a sandwich baggie, and then voila!✨...the duvet cover is perfectly placed on the duvet in under 2 minutes!🙌🏻 And you can do this technique on your bed instead of the floor if you want. 😉 Link to products/outfit: http://liketk.it/2LMSl

node.title: How to put on a duvet cover in under 2 minutes!

node.text: This is a beautiful home we toured today by Darling Homes in the Montgomery Farms neighborhood in Allen, TX. This is a 4 bedroom home (option for 5th bedroom) with about 5,000 square feet of living space. My favorite part of the home was the large open living room and kitchen space with all the floor to ceiling windows overlooking the patio! I also LOVE that there was a huge pantry and even a prep kitchen! Check out the IGTV video for the full tour of this beautiful home! What is your favorite part of this home?!!

node.title: Model Home Tour: Darling Homes, Allen, TX (priced from: $900K+)

This model home is in Arlington, Texas (right near Dallas. TX). This is a Toll Brothers Home in the Viridian master planned community. The model is called the “Valen”. node.text:
Can you believe it’s almost September?😱 Where did the summer go?! But now that September is here, it’s a bit more socially acceptable to have up Fall decor (lol! Not that it stopped me😂). So I went full Fall with my bedroom decor today! 🍁🍂🍁

Do you recognize this buffalo check quilt set? It’s actually the reverse side of the Primrose bedding set from my Walmart collection! I thought it would be perfect to use for Fall! It’s available now and linked on this post in the LTK app! 

And you’re also getting your first sneak peek at one of the new bedding sets that I’ll be launching soon at Walmart! 🤗🎉 This bed in a bag comforter set has cute little ties on the ends and button detailing across the middle! The set also will come with matching shams with ties, a complete sheet set and a set of three euro size decorative pillows (not shown)!! I’ll be sharing the whole set soon (it will come in several different colors). 

Finally, the Dahlia rug from my collection is on sale right now at Walmart!! The 8x10 size seen here is only $170!!! Amazing price for this beautiful rug!😱
http://liketk.it/3mQEV #falldecor #homedecor #bedroom #beddingsets #bedroomdecor #fall

Tonight, I’m sharing a few fall accents I added to my laundry room! 🍁#ad I love these vintage-look laundry storage tins and rolling laundry basket I got from @walmart! The storage tins are only $8 & $13 and I use them to store my laundry products like detergent, stain remover, fabric softener, etc. I’m sharing a bunch of my favorite laundry room decor from Walmart in my stories today (see last pic). 

🤗 Annnnnnd….here’s the FIRST exclusive sneak peek at the My Texas House candle collection coming soon to Walmart.com!! 🎉🎉🎉 Eeeek! Can’t wait for you to see the entire collection of these gorgeous 3-wick candles! Head to my stories for a closer look!

All sources, including the best-selling Lady Bird 3x5 rug (which is ON SALE!) are linked on the @shop.ltk app! http://liketk.it/3mIkO #walmarthome #liketkit #LTKhome

🙏🏻🙏🏻🙏🏻Saying prayers for all those in the path of hurricane Ida! Stay safe, friends!❤️❤️❤️

We made it back from Vegas and now trying to get back into the swing of everything (Laundry! School/Sports schedules! Laundry!😵‍💫)! I’m also planning my content for the next few weeks and came up with this list! Coming up soon… 

1) 🙌 A reveal of all the new MTH products we are launching at Walmart this fall/winter!

2) 🎥 A little update in our media room…new media cabinet just arrived! Decided against the super expensive Pottery Barn one I had been waiting to go on sale (it never did!😂).

3) 🛋 Our sofa needs a good cleaning…going to share the process of how I keep it looking brand new!

4) 🍁More fall decorating, including my front porch and mantel decor! 

5) 💻 The launch of my new website! 🤗 It’s just about done and it’s going to be way more user friendly so you can find anything you’re looking for much easier!

What are you looking forward to most? Or what would you like to see on my page this fall?! 

Entryway and fall decor linked on the LTK app 
http://liketk.it/3mxOS and on my website link in my bio 👉 @mytexashouse.

node.text:
Enjoying our last night here in Las Vegas! I wore this adorable dress today that I just got from @walmart! #ad I love the beautiful sage green color of the dress…perfect for fall! It also comes in a coral pink and plum/burgundy color. I linked my outfit in my stories and on the @shop.ltk app!

We are all done with the Vegas Market and ready to head home. Dusty and I decided that maybe we need to stay at a hotel aimed for older people like us next time we come to Vegas! 🙈 We are feeling our age this trip and our hotel, the Cosmopolitan, is really nice, but filled with all the youngin’s! 😆 We haven’t ever stayed at the Bellagio (where I’m standing) or the Paris hotel (in the background). Have y’all stayed at those hotels? Or which Vegas hotel would you recommend to a married couple that likes to eat good food and see good shows, but isn’t much into gambling or the nightlife??

#walmartfashion @walmartfashion

node.text:
Travel day! ✈️ Dusty and I flew to Las Vegas today to attend the Vegas Home Decor Market and meet with some of the MTH vendors! #ad Before I left I wanted to share a couple things…..
 1) I just got this beautiful new upholstered bench from @walmart to fill this big empty/awkward wall in the hallway between our bedroom & the living room. 

2) White faux pumpkin alert!!! 🚨 I wanted to let you know that Walmart has some great (and affordable) white and orange faux pumpkins right now both in store & online! You can never have too many in my opinion! Lol!! Hurry, these definitely will sell out soon!

It’s beginning to look a lot like fall!! 🍁🍂I’m starting to transform my house to a fall wonderland as I get ready to photograph my new fall decor collection for Walmart. It’s definitely a process and I’ll eventually be adding a plethora of pumpkins and possibly more garland, but you can at least get a peek at my color palette for this fall. I’m doing rusts, creams, browns and a touch of light pink! 

In my stories today, I’m sharing my process of changing out all my floral arrangements from summer to fall. I love how this one on my coffee table turned out! I linked my fave fall flowers and my living room decor on the LTK app! 

🍁Fall pillows seen in second pic are all from my new fall collection coming soon to Walmart.com!🍁

#LTKhome http://liketk.it/3m7GE

node.text:
Happy birthday to the most amazing husband and best friend, Dusty (@mrtexashouse)! This is always such a special week of the year for us as we always get to celebrate our wedding anniversary and Dusty’s birthday only days apart. And here, as promised, are our 20th anniversary photos we just had done when we were in Maui on the exact same beach as we had our wedding photos taken 20 years ago this week! The beach has changed a lot (as have the two of us!), but you can see the same tree limb in the background of the 1st two pics and the same old tree stump in the 2nd set of pics! 🥰 

No matter what life has thrown at us, both good and bad, over the past 20 years (actually 27 years together) we have done it together as partners, as friends, as each other’s “person.” I can’t imagine doing life without him! Happy birthday and happy anniversary, honey! 
I love you!😘 @mrtexashouse 

📸: Anniversary photography by Faith @ Colleen’s Captures in Maui

node.text:
Happy Monday! Do you remember this fall mantel look from a couple years ago where I went BIG with the pumpkin decor? 🤗😁 I was going through my old pictures and had forgotten I did this pastel color palette for fall 2 years ago! Can you guess if these were real or faux pumpkins and how long it took me to stack them that way? Tip▶️ I stacked up books to prop up the pumpkins in the back! 

This year I planned to do some beautiful warm and traditional colors for my fall decor, but now I’m thinking I may pull in some pretty pastels too! I will try to record my process of switching out my decor for fall and create some Reels on how I create my pumpkin displays and floral arrangements! What fall colors do love most? 

I linked my fall decor seen here or very similar products if no longer available on the LTK app! http://liketk.it/3lRJe
